results.definition: change or be different within limits
examples: Estimates for the losses in the earthquake range as high as $2 billion
Interest rates run from 5 to 10 percent
The instruments ranged from tuba to cymbals
My students range from very bright to dull

results.definition: move about aimlessly or without any destination, often in search of food or employment
examples: The cattle roam across the prairie
the laborers drift from one town to the next
They rolled from town to town

results.definition: have a range; be capable of projecting over a certain distance, as of a gun
examples: This gun ranges over two miles

results.definition: range or extend over; occupy a certain area
examples: The plants straddle the entire state

results.definition: lay out orderly or logically in a line or as if in a line
feed as in a meadow or pasture

examples: range the animals in the prairie

results.definition: assign a rank or rating to
examples: how would you rank these students?
The restaurant is rated highly in the food guide
at night in bed...his slowly ranging thoughts...encountered her
